05Dt 14:8 And also the pig, because even though its hoof is divided, it does not chew the cud. It is therefore unclean for you. You must not eat their meat or even touch their carcasses.
05Dt 14:9 "You may choose to eat from these creatures in the water£º you may eat anything with fin and scale, 
05Dt 14:10 but you may not eat anything without fin and scale, since it is unclean to you.
05Dt 14:11 "You may eat all clean birds. 
05Dt 14:12 But you must not eat from any of these£º the eagle, vulture, osprey, 
05Dt 14:13 buzzard, any kind of kite, 
05Dt 14:14 any kind of raven, 
05Dt 14:15 the ostrich, night hawk, seagull, any kind of falcon, 
05Dt 14:16 the little owl, the great owl, the horned owl, 
05Dt 14:17 the pelican, the carrion vulture, the cormorant, 
05Dt 14:18 the stork, any kind of heron, the hoopoe, and the bat. 
