05Dt 19:13 Have no pity on him, but totally purge the shedding of innocent blood from Israel so that life may go well with you.12
05Dt 19:14 "When you inherit the land that the Lord your God is about to give you, don't move your neighbor's boundary marker from where it was placed long ago."
05Dt 19:15 "The testimony of one person alone shall not suffice to convict anyone of any inequity, sin, or guilt. But the matter will stand on the testimony of two or three witnesses. 
05Dt 19:16 When a malicious witness takes the stand against a man and accuses him, 
05Dt 19:17 then both must stand with their dispute in the Lord's presence, the priests, and the judges at that time. 
05Dt 19:18 The judges will investigate thoroughly. If the false witness lies in testifying against his relative, 
05Dt 19:19 do to him just as he intended to do to his relative. By doing this you will purge evil from your midst. 
05Dt 19:20 When others hear of this, they will be afraid and will not do such an evil deed again in your midst. 
05Dt 19:21 Your eyes must not show pity - life for life, eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, and foot for foot."1916
05Dt 20:1 "When you go to war against your enemies and observe more horses, chariots, and soldiers than you have, don't be afraid of them, for the Lord your God who brought you out of the land of Egypt is with you.
