05Dt 21:16 then when he bequeaths his possessions to his sons, he must not give preference to the firstborn of the beloved wife over the firstborn of the unloved wife. 
05Dt 21:17 Instead, he must acknowledge the firstborn of the unloved wife by giving him double of everything he owns, because he is really the first fruit of his father's strength. The right of the firstborn belongs to him."
05Dt 21:18 "If a man has a stubborn son who does not obey his parents, and although they try to discipline him, he still refuses to pay attention to them, 
05Dt 21:19 then his parents shall seize him and bring him before the elders at the gate of his city. 
