05Dt 21:21 Then all the men of his city shall stone him with stones so that he dies. This is how you will remove this evil from among you. Then all Israel will hear of it and will be afraid."
05Dt 21:22 "If a man is guilty of a capital offense, is executed, and then is impaled on a tree, 
05Dt 21:23 his body must not remain overnight on the tree. You must bury him that same day, because cursed of God is the one who has been hanged on a tree. Don't defile your land that the Lord is about to give you as your inheritance."
05Dt 22:1 "When you see the ox or sheep of your fellow countryman straying, don't go away and leave them. Instead, be sure to return them to him. 
