05Dt 22:10 "Don't plow with an ox and a donkey yoked together. 
05Dt 22:11 "Don't wear material made from wool and linen mixed together.
05Dt 22:12 "Sew tassels for yourselves on the four corners of the garment with which you cover yourself."
05Dt 22:13 "Suppose a man marries a wife but after having sexual relations with her, he despises her, 
05Dt 22:14 invents charges against her, and defames her by saying, 'I have married this woman, but when I had sexual relations with her I found that she wasn't a virgin.'
05Dt 22:15 "Then the father of the young lady, along with her mother, shall bring evidence of the young lady's virginity to the elders at the gate. 
05Dt 22:16 The father of the young lady shall then say to the elders£º 'I have given my daughter to this man as a wife, but he despises her. 
05Dt 22:17 Now look, he has invented charges against her by saying, "I haven't found your daughter to be a virgin." But here is the proof of my daughter's virginity.' Then they are to spread the cloth before the elders of the city.
