05Dt 22:19 fine him 100 shekels of silver, and then give them to the young lady's father, because he had defamed a virgin of Israel. She shall remain his wife and he can't divorce her as long as he lives.22
05Dt 22:20 But if this charge is true, and the evidence of the young lady's virginity weren't found, 
05Dt 22:21 they are to bring her to the door of her father's house. Then the men of the city shall stone her with boulders until she dies for doing a detestable thing in Israel - acting like a prostitute while in her father's house. By doing this, you will remove this evil from among you.
05Dt 22:22 "If a man is caught having sexual relations with a married woman, then both of them must die - the man who had sex with the woman and the woman herself - so that this evil will be removed from Israel. 22
05Dt 22:23 "If a man meets a young virgin lady engaged to be married in the city and has sexual relations with her, 
05Dt 22:24 then the two must be brought to the city gate and there they must be stoned to death - the girl because she was in a city but did not cry out for help, and the man who abused a woman who was engaged to another man. By doing this you are to remove this evil from among you.
05Dt 22:25 "If a man meets a girl in the country who is engaged to be married and then rapes her, the man alone - the one who had sexual relations with her - must die. 
