05Dt 22:27 Since he found her in the country, the engaged girl may have cried out, but there was no one to rescue her.
05Dt 22:28 "However, if a man meets a girl who isn't engaged to be married, and he seizes her, rapes her, and is later found out, 
05Dt 22:29 then the man who raped her must give 50 shekels of silver to the girl's father. Furthermore, he must marry her. Because he had violated her, he shall not divorce her as long as he lives.
05Dt 22:30 "A man must not marry his father's wife, so that he will not dishonor his father's memory."
05Dt 23:1 "No man whose testicles have been crushed or whose penis has been cut off may participate in the assembly of the Lord. 
05Dt 23:2 Furthermore, no one born due to an illicit sexual relationship may participate in the assembly of the Lord, including his descendants to the tenth generation.1 
05Dt 23:3 "No Ammonite or Moabite may participate in the assembly of the Lord, and none of their descendants shall be admitted to the assembly of the Lord, to the tenth generation, 
05Dt 23:4 because they didn't come to meet you with food and water along the way as you were coming out of Egypt. Instead, they hired Beor's son Balaam from Pethor in Aram-naharaim to curse you. 
05Dt 23:5 However, the Lord your God didn't listen to Balaam. The Lord your God turned Balaam's curse into a blessing, because the Lord your God loves you. 
05Dt 23:6 Don't seek a peace treaty with them as long as you live.5
05Dt 23:7 "Don't detest Edomites, since they are related to you. Don't detest Egyptians, either, because you were strangers in their land. 
05Dt 23:8 Their grandchildren may participate in the assembly of the Lord."
05Dt 23:9 "When you are encamped for battle against your enemies, be on guard against every form of impropriety. 
05Dt 23:10 If someone among you becomes unclean due to nocturnal emissions, he must leave the camp and stay outside. 
05Dt 23:11 As evening approaches he must wash himself with water. Then at sunset, he may return to the camp.
05Dt 23:12 "Choose a place outside the camp for a latrine. 
05Dt 23:13 Include a spade among your equipment so that when you squat to relieve yourself, you can dig a hole and then cover your excrement. 
05Dt 23:14 For the Lord your God is on the move within your camp to deliver you and to hand your enemies over to you. Therefore your camp must be holy so that he will not see anything indecent among you and turn away from you."
05Dt 23:15 "Don't hand over a slave who escaped from his master when he runs to you. 
05Dt 23:16 Let him live among you wherever he chooses in any of your cities that he likes. Don't mistreat him."
05Dt 23:17 "There shall be no cultic prostitutes from among the daughters or the sons of Israel. 
05Dt 23:18 Don't bring the earnings of a female prostitute nor the income of a male prostitute into the house of the Lord your God as payment for any vow. Both of these are detestable to the Lord your God."
05Dt 23:19 "Don't charge interest to your relatives, whether for money, food, or for anything that has been loaned at interest. 
05Dt 23:20 You may charge interest to a foreigner, but don't charge interest to your relatives, so the Lord your God may bless you in everything you undertake in the land that you are about to enter and possess.
05Dt 23:21 "When you make a vow to the Lord your God, don't delay paying it, because the Lord your God will certainly demand payment from you, and then you will be guilty of sin. 
05Dt 23:22 But if you refrain from making a vow, then you won't be guilty. 
05Dt 23:23 Be sure you do whatever you promise, because you have given your word voluntarily to the Lord your God.
05Dt 23:24 "When you enter your countrymen's vineyard, you may eat the grapes to your satisfaction, but don't take any in a basket. 
05Dt 23:25 When you enter your countrymen's grain fields, you may pluck the grain with your hand, but don't put a sickle to his standing grain."
05Dt 24:1 "If a man chooses to enter into marriage with a woman, but she finds herself displeasing to him because he has found something objectionable about her, he must draw up divorce papers, hand them to her, and then send her out of his house. 
05Dt 24:2 If she goes out from his house, becomes the wife of another man, 
05Dt 24:3 and this second husband dislikes her, he, also, must draw up divorce papers, hand them to her, and then send her away from his house. Should the second husband die, 
05Dt 24:4 her first husband who married her and divorced her earlier must not remarry her, because she was defiled, since this is detestable to the Lord. Don't defile the land that the Lord your God is about to give you as a possession.2
05Dt 24:5 "When a man is newly married, he must not be sent out to war or have a related duty placed on him. Let him stay home for one year and be happy with his wife whom he has married.
05Dt 24:6 "Don't take a pair of millstones, especially the upper millstone, as collateral for a loan, because this means taking a man's livelihood.
05Dt 24:7 "If a man is found kidnapping his relative, a fellow Israelite, and mistreats or sells him, that kidnapper must die. By doing this, you will remove this evil from among you.
05Dt 24:8 "In cases of leprosy, be very careful to observe exactly what the Levitical priests instructed you. Carefully follow what I have commanded them. 
05Dt 24:9 Remember what the Lord your God did to Miriam along the way as you were coming out of Egypt."
05Dt 24:10 "When you loan something to your neighbor, don't enter his house to seize what he offered as collateral. 
05Dt 24:11 Stay outside and let the man to whom you made the loan bring it out to you. 
05Dt 24:12 If he is a poor man, don't go to sleep with his collateral in your possession. 
05Dt 24:13 Be sure to return his garment to him at sunset so that he may sleep with it, and he will bless you. It will be a righteous deed in the presence of the Lord your God.
05Dt 24:14 "Don't take advantage of a hired person who is poor and needy, whether he's your fellow citizen or a foreigner who lives in your city. 
05Dt 24:15 Pay his wages that same day before the sun sets, because he is poor and his livelihood depends on it. Otherwise, he may cry out to the Lord against you, and you will incur guilt."
05Dt 24:16 "Fathers must not be put to death on account of their children's sin; nor shall children die on account of their fathers' sin. Each person shall be put to death for his own sin.24
05Dt 24:17 "Don't deny justice to a foreigner or to an orphan, nor take a widow's garment as collateral for a loan. 
05Dt 24:18 Remember to observe this because you were slaves in Egypt, and the Lord your God redeemed you from there. That is why I am commanding you to do this.
05Dt 24:19 "When you are reaping in the field, and you overlook a sheaf, don't return to get it. Let it remain for the foreigner, the orphan, or the widow, in order that the Lord your God may bless everything you undertake.
05Dt 24:20 "When you harvest the olives from your trees, don't go back to the branches a second time. What remains is for the foreigner, the orphan, or the widow.
05Dt 24:21 "When you harvest the grapes in your vineyard, don't go back a second time. What remains are for the foreigner, the orphan, or the widow. 
05Dt 24:22 Remember to do this because you were slaves in the land of Egypt. That is why I'm commanding you to do this."
05Dt 25:1 "When there is a conflict between individuals, let them come to court to judge the case, decide who is innocent, and condemn the guilty person. 
05Dt 25:2 If the guilty person deserves a beating, the judge will make him lie down and be beaten in his presence with the number of lashes fit for his crime. 
05Dt 25:3 But he must not be beaten more than 40 lashes, because if he receives more than 40 lashes, your brother will be humiliated in your eyes.
05Dt 25:4 "Don't muzzle an ox while it is threshing grain."
05Dt 25:5 "When two brothers are living together and one of them dies without leaving a son, his widow must not be married outside the family to a foreigner. Instead, the brother-in-law must go to her, take her as his wife, and by doing so perform the duty of a brother-in-law. 
05Dt 25:6 The firstborn whom she will bear will continue the name of the dead brother, so his name will not be erased from Israel. 
05Dt 25:7 But if the man does not want to marry his brother's widow, then she must go to the elders at the city gate and declare, 'My husband's brother refuses to perform the duty of a brother-in-law in order to preserve the name of his brother in Israel. He is not willing to perform the duty of a brother-in-law.' 
05Dt 25:8 Then the elders of the city are to summon him and speak with him. If he insists on saying, 'I don't want to marry her,' 
05Dt 25:9 then she is to approach her brother-in-law in the presence of the elders, remove his sandal, spit in his face, and say in response, 'May this be done to the man who does not preserve the lineage of his brother.' 
05Dt 25:10 Then his family name in Israel will be known 'as the family of the one whose sandal was removed.'"
05Dt 25:11 "If two men are fighting together, and the wife of one comes to rescue her husband from the grasp of his assailant, and she reaches out and seizes his genitals, 
05Dt 25:12 cut off her hand. Don't show any pity."
05Dt 25:13 "Don't have different weights in your bag - one heavy and one light. 
05Dt 25:14 Don't have different measuring devices in your house - one large and one small. 
05Dt 25:15 You must have honest weights and measuring devices, so you may live long in the land that the Lord your God is about to give you, 
05Dt 25:16 for anyone who does these things - anyone who deals dishonestly - is detestable to the Lord your God."25
05Dt 25:17 "Remember what the Amalekites did to you along the road while you were coming out of Egypt, 
05Dt 25:18 how when you were very tired and weary, they lay in wait for you on the road and eliminated everyone who was lagging behind. They had no fear of God. 
05Dt 25:19 Therefore, when the Lord your God has given you rest from all your enemies who surround you in the land that he is about to give you to possess as an inheritance, you must completely erase the memory of the Amalekites from under heaven. Don't forget!"
05Dt 26:1 "When you arrive in the land that the Lord your God is about to give you as an inheritance, take possession of it and settle in it. 
05Dt 26:2 Gather all the first produce of the ground that you harvest from your land that the Lord your God is about to give you, place it in a basket, and bring it to the place where the Lord your God will choose to establish his name. 
05Dt 26:3 Approach the priest who is in charge at that time and say to him, 'I acknowledge today to the Lord your God that I've arrived in the land that the Lord promised our ancestors to give us.'
05Dt 26:4 "Then the priest will take the basket from you and place it in front of the altar of the Lord your God. 
05Dt 26:5 Then you are to affirm and declare in the presence of the Lord your God£º A wandering Aramean was my ancestor, who went down to Egypt and traveled there with very few family members, yet there he became a great, powerful, and populous nation. 
05Dt 26:6 But the Egyptians oppressed us, afflicted us, and assigned us to hard labor. 
05Dt 26:7 So we cried out to the Lord God of our ancestors, and he heard our cries and observed our affliction, trouble, and oppression. 
05Dt 26:8 The Lord brought us out of Egypt with his awesome power, with great terror, signs, and wonders. 
05Dt 26:9 And then we arrived at this place, and he gave this land to us, flowing with milk and honey. 
05Dt 26:10 Now, look - I brought the first produce of the land that you, Lord, have given me. Then set it in the presence of the Lord your God and worship him. 
05Dt 26:11 Rejoice with the Levites and the foreigner among you at all the good things that the Lord your God has given you and your family."
05Dt 26:12 "When you have finished your harvest, reserve the tithe in the third year (the year of the tithe), and give the entire tithe to the Levites, to the foreigners, to the orphans, and to the widows, so they may eat and be satisfied in your cities. 
05Dt 26:13 Then declare in the presence of the Lord your God£º 'I've removed the holy offering from my house and given it to the Levites, to the foreigners, to the orphans, and to the widows just as you have commanded me. I haven't violated or forgotten your commands. 
05Dt 26:14 I haven't eaten any part of it while mourning, nor removed any part of it while unclean, nor offered any of it to the dead. I've obeyed the voice of the Lord my God and did all that he commanded me. 
05Dt 26:15 Look down from your holy habitation in heaven and bless your people Israel and the land that you have given us, just as you promised our ancestors - a land flowing with milk and honey.'"
05Dt 26:16 "The Lord your God is commanding you this very day to observe these statutes and judgments. Be careful to obey them with all your heart and soul. 
05Dt 26:17 You have declared this very day that the Lord will be your God. You are to walk in his ways, keep his statutes, commands, and judgments, and obey his voice. 
05Dt 26:18 The Lord affirmed this day that you are his prized possession. Therefore observe his commands, 
05Dt 26:19 so he may elevate you far above all the nations that he has made. Then you will live to the praise, fame, and glory of God, and so be a nation that is holy to the Lord your God, as he has promised."2616
05Dt 27:1 Moses and the elders of Israel gave these orders to the people£º "Observe all of the commandments that I'm giving you today. 
05Dt 27:2 On the day you cross over the Jordan River to the land that the Lord your God is about to give you, set up large stones and coat them with plaster. 
05Dt 27:3 Then inscribe on them all the words of this law when you've crossed over into the land that the Lord your God is about to give you - a land flowing with milk and honey--just as the Lord God of your ancestors promised you.
05Dt 27:4 "When you have crossed the Jordan River, set up these stones about which I'm commanding you today on Mount Ebal, and coat them with plaster. 
05Dt 27:5 Then build an altar there to the Lord your God, an altar of stones that hasn't been worked with iron tools. 
05Dt 27:6 Build the altar to the Lord your God with uncut stones, then offer a burnt offering to him. 
05Dt 27:7 Offer a burnt offering there, then eat and rejoice in the presence of the Lord your God. 
05Dt 27:8 Inscribe on the stones plainly and distinctly all the words of this Law."5
05Dt 27:9 Then Moses and the Levitical priests spoke to Israel. They said, "Be quiet and listen, Israel! Today you have become the people of the Lord your God. 
05Dt 27:10 Listen to his voice and carry out his commands and statutes that I'm giving you today."
05Dt 27:11 Moses commanded the people that day saying, 
05Dt 27:12 "When you cross the Jordan River, these tribes will stand on Mount Gerizim to bless the people - Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Joseph, and Benjamin. 
05Dt 27:13 The tribes of Reuben, Gad, Asher, Zebulon, Dan, and Naphtali will stand on Mount Ebal to pronounce the curse. 
05Dt 27:14 "The Levites will declare in a loud voice to every Israelite:
05Dt 27:15 'Cursed is the one who makes a sculptured or cast image - a detestable thing to the Lord, the work of a craftsman - and sets it up secretly.' "Then all the people will respond by saying, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:16 'Cursed is the one who treats his father and mother with dishonor.' "Then all the people will respond by saying, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:17 'Cursed is the one who moves his neighbor's boundary stone.' "Then all the people are to respond by saying, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:18 'Cursed is the one who misleads a blind person on the road. "Then all the people are to respond by saying, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:19 'Cursed is the one who perverts justice due the foreigner, the orphan, or the widow.' "Then all the people are to respond by saying, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:20 'Cursed is the one who has sexual relations with his father's wife, because he has disgraced his father. "Then all the people are to respond by saying, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:21 'Cursed is the one who has sexual relations with any animal. "Then all the people are to respond by saying, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:22 'Cursed is the one who has sexual relations with his sister, the daughter of his father or mother. "Then all the people are to respond by saying, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:23 'Cursed is the one who has sexual relations with his mother-in-law. "Then all the people are to respond by saying, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:24 'Cursed is one who strikes his neighbor secretly. "Then all the people are to respond by saying, 'Amen!'27
05Dt 27:25 "Cursed is one who accepts a bribe to kill an innocent person. "Then all the people are to respond by saying, 'Amen!'
05Dt 27:26 "Cursed is the one who doesn't uphold the words of this Law and observe them. "Then all the people are to respond by saying, 'Amen!'"
05Dt 28:1 "Indeed, if you diligently obey the Lord your God to carry out all his commands that I'm giving you today, then the Lord your God will set you high above all the nations of the earth. 
05Dt 28:2 Moreover, all these blessings will come upon you in abundance, if you obey the Lord your God:
05Dt 28:3 "Blessed shall you be in the city and blessed shall you be in the country.
05Dt 28:4 "Blessed shall your children be, as well as the produce of your land, the offspring of your beasts and cattle, and the offspring of your flock.
05Dt 28:5 "Blessed shall be your grain basket and your kneading bowl.
05Dt 28:6 "Blessed shall you be in your comings and goings."
05Dt 28:7 "The Lord will make your enemies, who rise against you and attack from one direction, to flee from you in seven directions.
05Dt 28:8 "The Lord will send blessings for you with regard to your barns and everything you undertake. Indeed, he will bless you in the land that the Lord your God is about to give you.
05Dt 28:9 "The Lord will assign you to be a holy people for himself, just as he promised you, as long as you keep his commands and walk in his ways.
05Dt 28:10 "Then all the people of the earth will observe that the name of the Lordisproclaimed among you, and they will fear you.
05Dt 28:11 "The Lord will show his abundant goodness with respect to your children, the offspring of your animals, and the produce of your farmland that he promised your ancestors he would give you.
05Dt 28:12 "The Lord will open his rich treasury, the heavens, to release rain upon your land in season and bless everything you undertake so that you'll lend to many nations but won't borrow.
05Dt 28:13 "The Lord your God will make you the head and not the tail - placing you above and not beneath - if you obey the commands of the Lord your God that I'm giving you today to keep and observe. 
05Dt 28:14 Do not deviate from any of his commands that I'm giving you today - neither to the right nor the left - to follow and serve other gods."
05Dt 28:15 "But if you don't obey the Lord your God and faithfully carry out all his commands and statutes that I'm giving you today, then all these curses will come upon you and overwhelm you.
05Dt 28:16 "Cursed shall you be in the city and cursed shall you be in the country.
05Dt 28:17 "Cursed shall be your grain basket and your kneading bowl.
05Dt 28:18 "Cursed shall your children be, as well as the produce of your land, the offspring of your beasts and cattle, and the offspring of your flock.
05Dt 28:19 "Cursed shall you be in your comings and goings." 
05Dt 28:20 "The Lord will send the curse among you, will confuse you, and will rebuke you in everything you undertake until you are destroyed and perish quickly because of your evil deeds, since you will have forsaken him. 
05Dt 28:21 The Lord will cause you to be ill with long-lasting diseases until you are wiped out from the land that you are entering to possess. 
05Dt 28:22 The Lord will afflict you with tuberculosis, fever, inflammation, high fever, drought, blight, and mildew. These will attack you until you are completely destroyed. 
05Dt 28:23 The sky above your head will become bronze while the ground beneath you will become iron. 
05Dt 28:24 The Lord will change the rain on your land to powder and dust. It will come down from the sky until you are exterminated."22
05Dt 28:25 "The Lord will cause you to be defeated by your enemies. You'll go out against them in one direction, but you'll flee from them in seven directions. Consequently, you'll be in a state of great terror throughout all the kingdoms of the earth. 
05Dt 28:26 Your dead bodies will be food for the birds of the sky and the wild animals of the earth, with no one to chase them away.25
05Dt 28:27 "The Lord will afflict you with the boils of Egypt, with tumors, skin disease, and festering rashes, and none of them will be curable. 
05Dt 28:28 The Lord will afflict you with insanity, blindness, and mental confusion. 
05Dt 28:29 As a result, you'll wander aimlessly in broad daylight just as a blind person wanders in darkness. You won't prosper in life. Instead you'll be oppressed and plundered all day long, with no deliverer.
05Dt 28:30 You'll be engaged to a woman, but another man will rape her. You'll build a house but you won't live in it. You'll plant a vineyard but you won't harvest it. 
05Dt 28:31 Your ox will be slaughtered in front of you, and you won't be able to eat it. Your donkey will be stolen from you while you watch and won't be returned to you. Your flock of sheep will be handed to your enemies and there will be no deliverer. 
05Dt 28:32 Your sons and daughters will be given to another people while you watch, and you won't be able to approach them at all, and you'll be powerless to help.
05Dt 28:33 A people whom you don't know will devour what your land and labor produces. You'll be only oppressed and discouraged continually 
05Dt 28:34 until you are driven insane from what your eyes will see.
05Dt 28:35 "The Lord will inflict you with incurable boils on your knees and legs, and from the sole of your foot to the top of your head.
05Dt 28:36 "The Lord will banish you and your king whom you will appoint over you to go to a nation that neither you nor your ancestors have known, and there you'll serve other gods of wood and stone. 
05Dt 28:37 You'll become a desolation and a proverb, and you'll be mocked among the people where the Lord will drive you."
05Dt 28:38 "You'll plant many seeds in a field, but your harvest will be small because the locust will consume it. 
05Dt 28:39 You'll plant a vineyard, but you won't drink wine or harvest any grapes, because worms will consume it. 
05Dt 28:40 You'll have olive trees throughout your territory, but you won't be able to anoint yourself with oil, because the olives will drop off the trees. 
05Dt 28:41 You'll bear sons and daughters, but they won't belong to you, because they'll go into captivity. 
05Dt 28:42 Whirling locusts will consume every tree and the produce of your land. 
05Dt 28:43 The foreigner in your midst will be elevated higher and higher over you, while you are brought low little by little. 
05Dt 28:44 He will lend to you, but you won't lend to him. He'll be the head, but you'll be the tail. 
05Dt 28:45 All these curses will come upon you and will overwhelm you until you are exterminated, because you didn't obey the Lord your God to keep his commands and statutes, which he had commanded you. 
05Dt 28:46 These curses will serve as a sign and wonder for you and your descendants as long as you live."45
05Dt 28:47 "Because you didn't serve the Lord your God joyfully and wholeheartedly, despite the abundance of everything you have, 
05Dt 28:48 you'll serve your enemies whom the Lord your God will send against you. You will serve in famine and in drought, in nakedness, and in lack of everything. They'll set a yoke of iron upon your neck until they have exterminated you.
05Dt 28:49 "The Lord will raise a distant nation against you from the other side of the earth. Swooping down like a vulture, 
05Dt 28:50 it will be a nation whose language you don't understand, whose stern appearance neither shows regard nor extends grace to anyone whether old or young. 
05Dt 28:51 Its army will consume the offspring of your animals and the produce of your soil until you are exterminated. They will leave you without your grain, wine, oil, the increase of your cattle, and the lamb of your flock, until you are completely destroyed. 
05Dt 28:52 They'll besiege all your cities until your high and fortified walls in which you have trusted collapse throughout the land. Indeed, they will besiege all your cities, which the Lord your God gave you.50
05Dt 28:53 "You'll eat your own children - the flesh of your sons and daughters, whom the Lord your God gave you - on account of the siege and the distress with which your enemy will oppress you. 
05Dt 28:54 Even the compassionate man among you - the very sensitive one - will look with evil in his eyes toward his brother, his beloved wife, and his surviving sons, whom he spared. 
05Dt 28:55 He will withhold from each of them the flesh of his sons that he is eating - since there will be nothing left - on account of the siege and distress with which your enemy will oppress you in all your cities. 
05Dt 28:56 The most tender and sensitive lady among you, who doesn't venture to touch the soles of her feet to the ground on account of her daintiness, will look with hostility in her eyes against her beloved husband, her sons, and her daughters. 
05Dt 28:57 She will eat her afterbirth and her newborn children secretly - since there will be nothing left - on account of the siege and distress with which your enemy will oppress you in your cities."28
05Dt 28:58 "If you aren't careful to observe all the words of this Law that have been written in this book, instructing you to fear this glorious and awesome name of the Lord your God 
05Dt 28:59 then he will inflict extraordinary plagues on you and your children, great and lasting plagues, and severe and lasting illnesses. 
05Dt 28:60 He will inflict on you all the diseases of Egypt that you dreaded, and they won't be curable. 
05Dt 28:61 Moreover, the Lord will inflict you with illnesses and plagues that were not written in this book of the Law, until you are exterminated. 
05Dt 28:62 Because you will not have obeyed the Lord your God, very few of you will be left - instead of you being as numerous as the stars in the heavens. 
05Dt 28:63 Just as the Lord delighted to prosper and increase you, so now the Lord will delight to destroy, exterminate, and banish you from the land that you are about to enter to possess."
05Dt 28:64 "He'll scatter you among the peoples from one end of the earth to the other, and there you'll serve other gods made of wood and stones, which neither you nor your ancestors have known. 
05Dt 28:65 Among those nations you'll have no rest. There'll be no resting place for the soles of your feet. Instead, the Lord will give you an anxious heart, failing eyesight, and a despairing spirit. 
05Dt 28:66 You'll cling to life, being fearful by both night and day, with no assurance of survival. 
05Dt 28:67 In the morning you'll say, 'I wish it were evening.' Yet in the evening you'll say, "I wish it were morning," on account of what you'll dread and what you'll see. 
05Dt 28:68 Finally, the Lord will bring you back to Egypt by ship, a place that I said you'll never see again. There you'll try to sell yourselves to your enemies as male and female slaves, but no one will buy you."
05Dt 29:1 Th05Dt 28:ese are the terms of the covenant, which the Lord commanded Moses to make with the Israelites in the land of Moab in addition to the covenant that he made with them in Horeb. 
05Dt 29:2 Moses called all Israel together and addressed them£º "You saw everything that the Lord did before your eyes in the land of Egypt to Pharaoh, to all his servants, and to his whole country. 
05Dt 29:3 Those great feats that you saw with your own eyes are signs and great wonders. 
05Dt 29:4 Yet to this day, the Lord hasn't given you a heart that understands, eyes that perceive, and ears that discern.2
05Dt 29:5 "Though I've led you for 40 years in the desert, neither your clothes nor your shoes have worn out. 
05Dt 29:6 You didn't have to eat bread or drink wine or an intoxicating drink, in order to know that I am the Lord your God. 
05Dt 29:7 Then you reached this place, where King Sihon of Heshbon and King Og of Bashan had come out to meet and fight with us, but we defeated them. 
05Dt 29:8 We captured their land and handed it as an inheritance to the Reubenites, the Gadites, and half the tribe of Manasseh. 
05Dt 29:9 Therefore, keep the terms of this covenant, carrying them out so that you'll be wise in everything you do."
05Dt 29:10 "All of you are standing today in the presence of the Lord your God - the heads of your tribes, your elders, your magistrates, all the men of Israel, 
05Dt 29:11 along with your children, your wives, even the foreigner in your camp, including the woodchopper and the water drawer - 
05Dt 29:12 to enter into a covenant with the Lord your God and into the oath that he is about to make with you today, 
05Dt 29:13 so that he will elevate you to be a people for him. And he will be God to you, just as he promised you and swore to your ancestors Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. 
05Dt 29:14 Now, I'm not making this covenant and oath with you alone, 
05Dt 29:15 but with whoever is here with us standing in the presence of the Lord our God today, as well as with those who aren't here with us today."
05Dt 29:16 "Now, you know how we lived in the land of Egypt and how we traveled through the territory of other nations. 
05Dt 29:17 You have seen their detestable practices, their idols of wood, stone, silver, and gold that they had with them. 
05Dt 29:18 Be alert so there is no man, woman, family, or a tribe whose heart is turning away from the Lord your God to go and serve the gods of those nations. "Be alert so there will be no root among you that produces poisonous and bitter fruit, 
05Dt 29:19 because when such a person hears the words of this oath, he will bless himself and say£º 'I will have a peaceful life, even though I'm determined to be stubborn.' By doing this he will be sweeping away both watered and parched ground alike.'
