102Sm 22:1 David composed the words of this song to the Lord the very day the Lord delivered him from the domination of all of his enemies, including from Saul's hands. 
102Sm 22:2 This is what he said£º Lord, you are my stone stronghold and my fortified place; you are continually delivering me.
102Sm 22:3 He is my God, my strong stone - in him I will find my refuge? my shield, the strength of my salvation, my high tower, my way of escape, and the one who is saving me. You will save me from violence.
102Sm 22:4 As I am praising him, I will call out to the Lord, and I will be saved from my enemies.
102Sm 22:5 Because deadly breakers engulfed me, while torrents of abuse from the ungodly overwhelmed me.
102Sm 22:6 Binding ropes from Sheol entangled me while lethal snares hindered me.
102Sm 22:7 I cried out to the Lord in the middle of my troubles; I cried out to my God. He listened to my voice from his sanctuary, and my call for help was heard.
