102Sm 22:12 The darkness around him was his canopies - amassed water was his overhanging clouds!
102Sm 22:13 From the shining light that was his presence coals of fire blazed into flame!
102Sm 22:14 The Lord roared from heaven! The Most High let his voice be heard!
102Sm 22:15 He launched his arrows and scattered them - his lightning routed them.
102Sm 22:16 The currents of the sea were revealed and the foundations of the world were exposed at the rebuke of the Lord and at the blazing breath from his nostrils!
102Sm 22:17 He sent for me from on high! He grabbed hold of me, drawing me out of deep water.
102Sm 22:18 He rescued me from my strong enemy - from those who continually hate me, since they were stronger than I.
102Sm 22:19 They confronted me when I was in trouble, but the Lord remained my support!
102Sm 22:20 He brought me to a wide open area, rescuing me because he was pleased with me!
102Sm 22:21 The Lord dealt with me according to my righteousness, rewarding me according to the degree of my innocence,
102Sm 22:22 because I have kept the Lord's way - I haven't willfully abandoned my God - 
102Sm 22:23 and because all of his decrees remain in my thoughts, I have not turned aside from his statutes,
102Sm 22:24 I have been innocent before him, and I've kept myself from incurring guilt.
102Sm 22:25 The Lord has repaid me according to my righteousness, that is, according to my clean standing as he looks at me.
102Sm 22:26 In the company of the gracious you demonstrate your gracious love. In the company of the blamelessly valiant you demonstrate your blamelessness.
102Sm 22:27 In the company of the pure you demonstrate your purity. In the company of the perverted you will appear to be perverse.
102Sm 22:28 You save the nation who is humble but your eyes watch the proud, to bring them down.
102Sm 22:29 For you are my lamp, Lord, the Lord who illuminates my darkness.
102Sm 22:30 By you I devastate armies, by my God I scale walls.
102Sm 22:31 This God! His way is perfect! What the Lord declares proves true. He shields everyone who flees for protection to him!
102Sm 22:32 For who is God apart from the Lord?And who is a Rock, apart from our God - 
102Sm 22:33 This God is my strong place of valor! He has made my life blameless.
102Sm 22:34 He has made my feet like those of a deer, setting me secure on his high places!
102Sm 22:35 He has trained my hands for battle readiness - I can bend a bow made out of bronze.
102Sm 22:36 He has equipped me with the shield that is your salvation, Your gentleness has made me great.
102Sm 22:37 You've made room beneath me for my footsteps, and my feet didn't slip.
102Sm 22:38 I pursued my enemies and conquered them; I didn't return until they were consumed.
102Sm 22:39 I devoured them, striking them down until they could not get up again. They fell beneath my feet.
102Sm 22:40 You strengthened me with valor sufficient for the battle; you made those who rebelled against me fall beneath me.
102Sm 22:41 You made my enemies turn and run, - that is, those who hate me - and I destroyed them!
102Sm 22:42 They looked around, but there was no one to save them - they looked to the Lord, but he paid no attention!
102Sm 22:43 I pulverized them to powder, like the dust of the earth; I crushed them, stomping on them like mud on a street.
102Sm 22:44 You delivered me from civil war among my own people. You preserved me as head of the nations. People whom I had never known served me!
102Sm 22:45 Foreigners came cringing to me; they obeyed as soon as they heard me.
102Sm 22:46 Foreigners lost their courage, coming trembling from their strongholds.
102Sm 22:47 The Lord lives! Blessed be my Rock,  and may my God be exalted, the Rock who is my salvation!
102Sm 22:48 The God who keeps on avenging me, subjugating people beneath me,
102Sm 22:49 delivering me from my enemies. You exalted me above those who rebelled against me, delivering me from violent men.
102Sm 22:50 Because of all of this I will praise you among the nations, Lord, and I will sing praises to your name!
102Sm 22:51 Great is the salvation he brings to his king, showing gracious love to his anointed, to David and to his offspring forever.
